        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 8:58PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 858 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Union, or 6 miles southwest of Jonesville, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jonesville, Pacolet, Pauline, Croft State Park, Pacolet Mills,
Buffalo, Saratt, and Union.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
